        a: `It is a mature one. The Seven of Pentacles is rarely dramatic, romantic or fast-moving, but it is a deeply supportive card for relationships built on the long view. It honours patience, sustained investment and the wisdom of pausing to assess rather than impulsively re-planting. Couples who can stop, look at the field together and adjust their work tend to grow remarkable partnerships. The risk is impatience — uprooting something simply because it is taking longer than expected — or its opposite, leaning on the hoe forever without doing the next round of work.`,
